content.description: Simply follow bolt line. Tends to stay wet after rain.
Moderate slab climb between Pro Bono and Super Slab. Crux comes pulling the roof and a thin section right above it.
content.location: Left of Super Slab, right of Pro Bono. 5th bolted line in Super Slab Sector

content.description: Start just right of Slab Master.   Climb to first high bolt. follow 2 more bolts then through a break in the tree (sling) ledge above. Climb 2 more bolts step left and climb right facing flake to top.
One of the best at Safe Harbor, would be a popular slab climb anywhere. Climb to the high first bolt, then to the super fun thin crux above the roof.
Starts up a short-but-interesting dihedral to reach a shared ledge with "Quaranteenage...Turtles." From the ledge, make a high clip and crank a brief steep section leading to a pleasant slab above.
content.location: Left facing dihedral 20' left of Quaranteenage Mutant Ninja Turtles. The semi-vegetated wall just left of the main Super Slab routes.

content.description: Exciting slab with a couple of face holds. Start the climb about 8' to the right of Super Slab and go straight up the face. There are six bolts plus the anchors.
content.location: The middle climb on the Super Slab Sector directly to the right of Super Slab.

content.description: Move up the low angle slab to a crux bulge near 3rd bolt. Continue up fun, easy terrain to the finish.
content.protection: 6 bolts. Two bolt anchor with rings.
6 bolts plus hangars and chains at top

content.description:
The route's full name is, 

"Li'l Jerry is a good name for a fat squirrel". Don't ask, had to be there.

 Start under a short chossy band that is sometimes damp 20' right of Your Mother. Climb said band to first high bolt. Continue following bolts up corners and ledges to a blank head wall at the last bolt. You can use a small pocket out left about 3 feet from the bolt line or small side pulls out right about 3 feet from the bolt line. Or, you could go direct using tiny face holds and tiny feet ( 5.10)

  Directly above the right hand anchor bolt is a decent clipping hold for the anchors.
content.protection: 6 bolts and 2 bolt anchor. The first bolt is positioned on good rock, but its location means you should probably extend it so the lower carabiner is just below the small "lip".

content.description: Climbs around the classic Super Slab (5.10d) in Safe Harbor South.
